**Correction/Refinement of the Statement:**
The statement you provided is likely a misremembered or simplified version of a specific observation:
> "The only time the digits invert (roughly) is at **16°C** (which is **61°F**)."

There is **no** pattern where "every 12°C" the digits invert. If you add 12 to 16, you get 28°C.
*   $28^\circ\text{C} = (28 \times 1.8) + 32 = 50.4 + 32 = 82.4^\circ\text{F}$.
*   Digits of 28 are 2, 8. Digits of 82 are 8, 2.
*   **Wait!** $28^\circ\text{C}$ is approximately **$82^\circ\text{F}$**. The digits **are** inverted!

